track_notes: Plenty of parking at Glen Afton Filter Station. Leave the main path at waymark to climb up to the right and reach the Wind Farm tracks as far as Millaneoch Hill, from there quad tracks and moor until you cut across to reach another wind farm access track near the summit. The last section to the trig is easy moorland. Trig point with open top to take your pole.
track_title: Mostly graded wind farm tracks walked - upward track

track_notes: Further but easier using the track we found that goes around Wedder Hill rather than up and then down it.
track_title: A slight difference by going round Wedder Hill

track_notes:
This route sets off the Blackcraig Hill first.

From the parking at Blackcraig follow the track to Blackcraig Hill. Continue on over Blacklorg Hill to the line of Pylons. You can decide here if you want to do the circuit over Alwat and Alhang. I elected to follow the road down and then up the Afton Water valley to the last sheep fold then via Millanoch Hill to Windy Standard. The return is mainly on the windfarm roads. Walk time about 6h with a day of 11hr for activations and other stops.
track_title: Blackcraig Hill and Windy Standard in one walk
